      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering a museum-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the iconic S54B32 atmospheric inline-six. This powerplant utilizes six individual throttle bodies and Double VANOS variable valve timing to produce a linear torque curve and a visceral 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a factory-calibrated M-Variable limited-slip differential. Critically, the rear subframe has been professionally reinforced, and the rod bearing service is fully documented to ensure mechanical longevity. The chassis retains its factory-spec torsional rigidity, riding on a pristine suspension setup that preserves the legendary 50/50 weight distribution. Every component, from the VANOS solenoid to the differential bushings, operates within original tolerances, presenting a turnkey platform for the discerning collector.",
